				"img": "icons/magic/unholy/strike-hand-glow-pink.webp",
				"description": "<p>A faintly shimmering phantasmal hand appears at a point you choose within range. It remains until you dismiss it as an action, or until you move more than 30 feet from it.</p><p>You can use an action to control the hand and direct it to do any of the following:</p><ul><li>manipulate an object.</li><li>open an unlocked container or door.</li><li>stow or retrieve items from unlocked containers.</li></ul><p>The hand cannot attack, use magic items, or carry more than 10 pounds.</p>",
				"descriptionOutputs": [
					"action"
				]
			}
		},
		"description": "<p>This ornate bracer fits over the stump of a missing hand. You can use a mental command at any time (no action required) to summon a spectral, skeletal hand from the end of the bracer, allowing the user to function as though they had a natural hand in its place. You may also dismiss the hand, if desired (no action required). Finally, the hand can function as per the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.mocigztrqyoks506]{Mage Hand} spell for up to an hour per day. The hour need not be continuous. While the hand is used this way, you lose the use of the hand as a normal hand until it returns.</p>",
